Demo program to download and serve yahoo finance data via a rest api.

Uses yfinance api to download historical data from yahoo finance.

Utilities:

1. yfetch: downloads data from yahoo finance using yfinance
           and saves individual tickers as parquet (compression=gzip)
           files split by year. 

2. yserv:  runs a rest service using gunicorn[uvicorn[fast-api]] and provides
           the following end-points:
           a. tickers/: 
                       get currently saved tickers
           b. returns/{tickers}/{start_date}/{end_date}: 
                       get returns for ticker/s based on 
                       start/end dates
                       eg. returns/AAPL/20231004/20250926
                           returns/AAPL,AMZN,GOOG,META/20231004/20250926
           c. returns/{tickers}/{query_date}: 
                       get returns for ticker/s based on 
                       query date
                       eg. returns/NVDA/20250811
                           returns/NVDA,MSFT,AAPL,GOOG,AMZN,META/20250811

Requirements: included in requirements.txt (pip freeze)

usage:

 ./yfetch --help
Usage: yfetch.py [OPTIONS]

  yfinance downloader

Options:
  --tickers TEXT                  ric or , seperated list of rics  [default: N
                                  VDA,MSFT,AAPL,GOOG,AMZN,META,AVGO,TSLA,JPM,W
                                  MT,ORCL,LLY,V,MA,NFLX,XOM,JNJ,ABBV,PLTR,COST
                                  ,HD,BAC,PG]
  --period TEXT                   1d,5d,1mo,3mo,6mo,1y,2y,5y,10y,ytd,max,auto
                                  [auto: automatically detect last available
                                  date for present tickers and backfills till
                                  yesterday, please provide --start_date if
                                  there are any new tickers and auto option is
                                  used]
  --start_date [%Y%m%d|%Y-%m-%d|%Y.%m.%d|%Y/%m/%d|%d/%m/%Y|%Y-%m-%dD%H:%M:%S.000000000|%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S]
                                  query start date
  --end_date [%Y%m%d|%Y-%m-%d|%Y.%m.%d|%Y/%m/%d|%d/%m/%Y|%Y-%m-%dD%H:%M:%S.000000000|%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S]
                                  query end date
  --help                          Show this message and exit.


./yserv --help
Usage: yserv.py [OPTIONS]

  yfinance rest service

Options:
  --host TEXT     host  [default: 127.0.0.1]
  --port INTEGER  port  [default: 8000]
  --help          Show this message and exit.

Notes: 
1. postman available at http://host:port/docs when yserv is running
2. specify data dir location in app_config.yaml
